videos.title: Bob Ross: The Happy Painter - Full Documentary
videos.description:
Bob Ross fans! It’s ‘time’ for some happy trees, and we’ve got just what you need: https://pxlfy.me/BobRossWatchMightyMojoToys
You’ve seen him before - he's the quiet soft-spoken guy with the fuzzy afro hair painting mountains and trees with big brushes in a matter of seconds. Bob Ross is public television's most beloved personality and here is the behind-the-story look at his journey to becoming America's pop-culture icon.

This docu-story reveals the personal life of Bob Ross through the loving accounts of close friends and family, childhood photographs, rare archive footage - what you know: his unwavering dedication to wildlife for example, and what you don't know: Bob Ross' straight hair, his fascination with fast cars, and so much more.

You'll see rare film clips of Bob Ross with mentor William Alexander, and the very first rough-cut Joy of Painting episode. And you'll learn how one little TV commercial to advertise local painting classes slowly turned this gentle-mannered fellow from simple beginnings into a viral phenomenon that continues to allow millions around the world to realize their dream of becoming an artist.

Enjoy fascinating interviews and insights from some famous Bob Ross enthusiasts too, such as talk show pioneer Phil Donahue, film stars Jane Seymour and Terrence Howard, Chef Duff Goldman, and country music favorites Brad Paisley and Jerrod Niemann.

Bob Ross: The Happy Painter is presented in three parts: The Man, The Television Artist, and His Legacy.

videos.title: "I'm going to put a little water line in there. Just like so." - Bob Ross (Blue Winter)
videos.description:
"Take a little Liquid White, mix it with a little of the Titanium White, just to thin it down, because a thin paint will stick better. Right over here, I'm going to put a little water line in there. Just like so. There we are. Act like you're trying to cut a hole right through the canvas. Really get in there." - Bob Ross 
"Blue Winter" 1990 (Season 21 | Episode 10): https://youtu.be/liR0gS0sZY0

#shorts #bobross #quotes

videos.title: "There'd be a lot of fantastic little creatures..."
videos.description:
#shorts #shortvideo #shortsyoutube #shortsfeed #bobross #quotes

videos.title: "I could create any kind of world that I wanted..."
videos.description:
#shorts #bobross #painting
"Think that's what attracted me to painting so much. I could create any kind of world that I wanted. Nothing hurts here, no pain, nobody's unhappy, it's a pleasant place. Everything's new here." - Bob Ross (1987) "Mountain Summit"

Season 13, Episode 10

videos.title: "Painting is such an individual thing..."
videos.description:
"Painting is such an individual thing, and that's the way it should be. That's the way it should be. Everybody sees nature through different eyes, and the way you see it is the way it should be painted." Season 24 Episode 10

#shorts #bobross #bobrosspainting #painting #art

videos.title: "Just let your imagination take you to worlds that exist only in your mind..."
videos.description:

videos.title: "You know how those little rascals are."
videos.description:
"If you had two trees there, sooner or later, you'd have a third one. You know how those little rascals are. You've got to watch them." - Bob Ross (Season 12 | Episode 2 | "Mountain Reflections" | 1988) 

#shorts #bobross #painting #art
tags: bob ross quote of the day

videos.title: "Everyone's happy. That's what I'm looking for."
videos.description:
"There's nothing but good things here. You listen to the news sometimes and it really depresses you. Somebody got hurt, somebody else got shot or killed, and you can go to your easel and you can make the kind of world that makes you happy. There's no violence, no one's hurt here. Everyone's happy. Everyone's happy. That's what I'm looking for." 
- Bob Ross (Season 7 | Episode 2 | "Secluded Lake" | 1986)
tags: Bob Ross quote of the day

videos.title: "There it is. Look at that. That easy..."
videos.description:
"Now we want a big crashing wave here that's churning over and, watch, watch, see there? There it is. Look at that. That easy. That easy." - Bob Ross "Secluded Beach" 1987 (Season 9 | Episode 6) 

#shorts #bobross #bobrosspainting #painting #art #shortsfeed #shortsyoutube #shortsvideo

videos.title: "See he really got big and strong. Big old tree."
videos.description:
"I want a big tree there. This son of a gun, boy, the sun shined on him and he got a lot of water. Life was good to him. See he really got big and strong. Big old tree." - Bob Ross ("Mountain River" | Season 14 | Episode 5 | 1988)

http://www.BobRoss.com

#shorts #bobross #bobrosspainting #painting #art #shortsfeed #shortsyoutube #shortsvideo

videos.title: "We'll give him a little friend. This is Charlie."
videos.description:
"There is a happy evergreen that lives, lives, right there. Just push him right out of your brush. There he is, and we don't want him to get lonely. We'll give him a little friend. This is Charlie. This is Charlie." 
- Bob Ross ("Mountain Splendor" | 1985 | Season 7 | Episode 8) 

#shorts #bobross #bobrosspainting #painting #art #shortsfeed #shortsyoutube #shortsvideo
tags: bob ross quote of the day

videos.title: "Painting should make you happy."
videos.description:
"And painting, painting should make you happy. If it doesn't make you happy, you're doing the wrong thing." 
- Bob Ross ("Country Cabin" | 1987 | Season 11 | Episode 2)

videos.description:

#shorts #bobross #bobrosspainting #painting #art #shortsfeed #shortsyoutube #shortsvideo

("Mountain Stream" | 1987 | Season 11 | Episode 1)

videos.title: "I worked for a store one year at Christmas. They gave me several exotic pets."
videos.description:
"When I was just a child I had an alligator for a pet. Years and years ago. I worked for a store one year at Christmas. And instead of paying me money, I was only about 10 years old. They gave me several exotic pets. And one of them was an Alligator. And he was only about a foot long when they gave him to me. I'll never forget I took that rascal home and I wasn't that popular with my mother when I dropped her onto the living room floor out of a big ol' bag. And I kept him for about a year/year and a half. And he grew to about close to two to three feet long but he got mean. I don't think you could make a pet out of an alligator so I took him down to one of the local lakes and let him loose. Chances are he's still there today, sure he, by now he's probably huge and scarin' swimmers to death." 
- Bob Ross "Cypress Swamp" 1992 | Season 25 | Episode 8

videos.title: Happy Painting, My Friend | The Joy of Bob Ross - A Happy Little Podcast™
videos.description:
#shorts #bobross #painting 
The Joy of Bob Ross - A Happy Little Podcast™
Episode 9: Happy Painting, My Friend
Learn more: https://bobross.com/podcast

Chris Taylor is the first person I've interviewed for the podcast who met Bob Ross at a young age. Chris is a true Midwestern gentleman, soft spoken and polite -- but the biggest takeaway from our conversation was how much Bob encouraged Chris' artistic side from the moment they met. There were no stakes, no cameras -- and here was a real-life story of a mentor molding a young apprentice.  

"I feel Bob every step of the way," Chris says, describing his career not only as a CRI® but also as a Senior Director of Sports Production at Ball State University in Indiana.  Me too, Chris. Me too.

videos.title: The Joy of Bob Ross Twitch | Episode 20 | The Joy of Bob Ross - A Happy Little Podcast®
videos.description:
If you play video games, you probably know what #Twitch is. Over the past few years, the live streaming platform for gamers has expanded into a space for creators and artists to share their talents and their passions -- and on Twitch, it turns out that millions find joy in watching #BobRoss
 
Jessie Mason and Amanda Burns are both CRI®s who paint like Bob on Twitch, sharing stories about their respective journeys to the Bob Ross Workshop during a pandemic, an amusing tale about teaching actor Owen Wilson to paint a landscape, and proudly exclaiming their love for Bob, gaming, and geekery. 

The Joy of Bob Ross - A Happy Little Podcast®

videos.title: Brush Strokes | Official Trailer
videos.description:
Join now here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCxcnsr1R5Ge_fbTu5ajt8DQ/join

Now announcing a new digital membership on the official Bob Ross YouTube channel, Brush Strokes!

Members will receive access to exclusive tutorial content, demonstrated by our master CRI®’s Nicholas Hankins, Carolyn Saletto and Doug Hallgren. We’ll be diving deep into classic Bob Ross techniques like never before, including new full one hour painting guides. In addition, each month our master CRI®’s sit down to discuss a variety of topics and analyze episodes of The Joy Of Painting. Members will also receive custom emojis to use during live streams and premieres, access to live stream chat, channel badges to honor their support, and exclusive discounts on Bob Ross products.

Membership availability begins Thursday, March 6th. We're thrilled to announce this new endeavor and hope you'll join us soon!

Anyway you choose to enjoy, we invite you! Welcome, to Brush Strokes!

http://www.BobRoss.com
